Ac1 - write a program in java to extract all words from any file.display all words on screen and also save the same words in some out file. Use 4 command line arguments.
Ex: suppose our program file name=word_extraction.java
Name of word file=word_extraction.java
Run your code as follows:
C:\java\bin>java word_extraction
Word_extraction.java wordfile.java <enter>
…image…
import java.io.*;
import java.util.Scanner;

class word_extraction_2
{
public static void main(String[] args) 
{
int argc,n,nw,ch;
int flag;
argc=args.length;
FileInputStream fp1=new FileInputStream(args[0]);
FileOutputStream fp2=new FileOutputStream(args[1]);
nw=0; //nw=no of words
flag=1;
n=0; //n=size of input file
while((ch=fp1.read()) !=-1)
{
if((ch>=65 && ch<=90) || (ch>=97 && ch<=122))
{
if(flag==1)
{
nw=nw+1;
flag=0;
}
System.out.print((char)ch);
fp2.write(ch);
}
else is(flag==0)
{
System.out.println();
fp2.write(10);
flag=1;
}
}
fp1.close();
fp2.close();
System.out.println("total no of words extracted=" +nw);
